samples.question: For every order, how many products does it contain, and what are the orders' statuses and ids?

samples.question: List the dates of the orders which were placed at the earliest time or have more than 1 items.
samples.final_sql: SELECT o.date_order_placed FROM Orders o JOIN Order_Items oi ON o.order_id = oi.order_id GROUP BY o.order_id HAVING o.date_order_placed = (SELECT MIN(date_order_placed) FROM Orders) OR COUNT(oi.order_item_id) > 1;

samples.question: What are the dates of the earliest order and the dates of all orders with more than 1 item?
samples.final_sql: SELECT MIN(date_order_placed) AS earliest_order_date FROM Orders; SELECT date_order_placed FROM Orders WHERE order_id IN (SELECT order_id FROM Order_Items GROUP BY order_id HAVING COUNT(order_item_id) > 1);

samples.question: Which customers did not make any orders? List the first name, middle initial and last name.

samples.question: WHat are the first and last names, and middle initials of all customers who did not make any orders?

samples.question: What are the id, name, price and color of the products which have not been ordered for at least twice?

samples.question: What are the ids , names , prices , and colors of all products that have been listed in less than two orders ?

samples.question: Which orders have at least 2 products on it? List the order id and date.

samples.question: What are the ids and dates of the orders with at least two products?

samples.question: Which product are listed in orders most frequently? List the id, product name and price.

samples.question: What are the ids, names, and prices of all products that are ordered most frequently?

samples.question: Which order have the least sum of the product prices. List the order id and sum.

samples.question: What is the order that total cost the least , and how much is the total cost ?
samples.final_sql: SELECT T1.order_id, SUM(T3.product_price) AS total_cost FROM Orders AS T1 JOIN Order_Items AS T2 ON T1.order_id = T2.order_id JOIN Products AS T3 ON T2.product_id = T3.product_id GROUP BY T1.order_id ORDER BY total_cost ASC LIMIT 1;
